			<description><![CDATA[<p>
FabFitFun is looking for an experienced, enthusiastic, and smart photo and video intern to start this December/Jan.<br />
<br />
You would be responsible for finding and editing photos for our daily articles. We have several photo sites to source from but we are looking for someone with a keen and a great aesthetic sense. In addition, we would love to find someone who can take original photos for FFF as well as edit product shots using photoshop.</p>
<p>
In addition, we plan to incorporate more video content in 2013 so we would like to find someone with an ability to shoot and edit short videos (between 3-10 minutes long per video). The videos will feature beauty and fitness tutorials, celeb interviews, red carpet events and more.</p>
<p>
This would be a great opportunity for those looking to add to their resume! In exchange for your hard work, we will provide credit for original photos and videos. You&rsquo;ll also learn what makes a media site successful and how to shoot for the web. Not to mention the opportunity to use your creativity and experience for a number of popular videos. We want and need your input!</p>
<p>
Editorial interns&rsquo; responsibilities include:</p>
<ul>
<li>
photoshop - edit product shots, put together beautiful collages, etc</li>
<li>
original photography for site</li>
<li>
photo selection for articles</li>
<li>
film and edit 3-10 minute shorts</li>
<li>
Require your equipment such a camera, video camera, soft box lighting (or other) and microphones (directional or lapel).</li>
<li>
edit short videos</li>
<li>
add opening, logo, text, links and music to videos</li>
<li>
adjust any sound or lighting issues</li>
</ul>
<p>
Qualifications:</p>
<p>
We are looking at recent college grads or current students &ndash; ideally in pursuit of a related degree (e.g.Video/Radio/Film, etc.). Candidates with film experience will be given preference.</p>
<p>
Please take a look at the current FabFitFun site and send us your portfolio.</p>
<p>
The FabFitFun internship program lasts 4 months.</p>
]]></description>
